Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhopdian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Aristeidas. The piece is probably trimmed, hence from Naukratis. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0068.29.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
